sv":["sauce"]},{"name":"parmigiano reggiano","amount":"40 g","pcsv":["protein"]},{"name":"parsley","amount":"to taste","pcsv":["veggie"]},{"name":"salt","amount":"to taste","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"black pepper","amount":"to taste","pcsv":["sauce"]}],"instructions":"1. Melt butter in pan over medium-low heat. Grate in onion and garlic cloves (or finely mince). Sauté for 1-2 minutes until softened and fragrant. 2. Add rice and stir to coat kernels in fat and lightly toast exterior. Add about 80% of cooking liquid (broth and water), reserving the rest. Turn heat to medium-high and bring to simmer. Stir once or twice, then reduce heat to low. Cover with lid and set timer for 10 minutes. 3. After 10 minutes, stir rice once or twice, cover, and set timer for another 10 minutes. 4. Test rice doneness. Add remaining cooking liquid as needed to reach desired consistency. Add more liquid for loose texture; use less or continue reducing for compact, sticky texture. 5. Stir in Parmigiano and remaining butter until creamy. Season with salt, black pepper, and fresh herbs to taste.","alternatives":[{"id":"r059","name":"Cacio e Pepe (The Foolproof Way)","name_zh":"芝士黑椒意面","cuisine":"Italian","cooking_method":"braise","effort_level":"medium","flavor_tags":["herby","rich","savory"],"serves":6,"pcsv_roles":{"sauce":["water","cornstarch","olive oil","black pepper, freshly cracked","salt"],"protein":["parmigiano reggiano","pecorino romano"],"carb":["spaghetti, bronze cut"]},"ingredients_have":[],"ingredients_need":["water","cornstarch","parmigiano reggiano","pecorino romano","olive oil","black pepper, freshly cracked","spaghetti, bronze cut","salt"],"ingredients":[{"name":"water","amount":"150 g","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"cornstarch","amount":"10 g (2 spoonfuls)","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"parmigiano reggiano","amount":"100 g (1 part)","pcsv":["protein"]},{"name":"pecorino romano","amount":"150 g (1.5 part)","pcsv":["protein"]},{"name":"olive oil","amount":"15 g (a spoonful)","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"black pepper, freshly cracked","amount":"to taste","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"spaghetti, bronze cut","amount":"a serving","pcsv":["carb"]},{"name":"salt","amount":"a sprinkle","pcsv":["sauce"]}],"instructions":"1. Make the cornstarch gel: Add cornstarch and water to a saucepan. Mix until dissolved with no clumps. Heat on low, whisking until just below simmer (180°F/82°C). Starch should thicken; stir to remove clumps and set aside. 2. Blend the sauce: Add cheeses, olive oil, and black pepper to a blender. Pulse once or twice, then pour in cornstarch gel. Blend into thick, stable emulsion. Store in fridge for 3-5 days if desired. 3. Boil the pasta: Boil salted water, add pasta, cook until al dente or slightly underdone. Reserve a cupful of pasta water before draining. 4. Combine the sauce: In a second pan off heat, add 2 heaping spoonfuls sauce and splash of pasta water per serving. Mix together. Add hot pasta and fold together. Turn heat to medium-low, slowly bring temperature up while tossing. Adjust consistency with more sauce or pasta water as needed. 5. Garnish & serve: Serve immediately on warmed plates with grated pecorino and fresh black pepper.","alternatives":[]},{"id":"r088","name":"Spinach Carbonara","name_zh":"菠菜卡邦尼意面","cuisine":"Italian","cooking_method":"braise","effort_level":"medium","flavor_tags":["herby","rich","savory","tangy"],"serves":6,"pcsv_roles":{"sauce":["water","cornstarch","olive oil","lemon juice","black pepper","salt","pasta water"],"veggie":["spinach","garlic","fresh basil"],"protein":["parmigiano reggiano"],"carb":["spaghetti"]},"ingredients_have":[],"ingredients_need":["water","cornstarch","spinach","parmigiano reggiano","garlic","olive oil","lemon juice","black pepper","salt","spaghetti","pasta water","fresh basil"],"ingredients":[{"name":"water","amount":"150 g","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"cornstarch","amount":"10 g","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"spinach","amount":"150 g","pcsv":["veggie"]},{"name":"parmigiano reggiano","amount":"100 g","pcsv":["protein"]},{"name":"garlic","amount":"3 cloves","pcsv":["veggie"]},{"name":"olive oil","amount":"2 spoonfuls","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"lemon juice","amount":"1/2 lemon","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"black pepper","amount":"a few sprinkles","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"salt","amount":"to taste","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"spaghetti","amount":"a serving","pcsv":["carb"]},{"name":"pasta water","amount":"as needed","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"fresh basil","amount":"for serving","pcsv":["veggie"]}],"instructions":"Step 1: Prepare the spinach\nSet a pot of water to boil. Meanwhile, mince the garlic, grate the parmesan, and gather the remaining ingredients. Fill a mixing bowl with ice water. Once the water has boiled, add the spinach and blanch for 45 seconds. Strain and add to the cold water to stop the cooking process. Transfer to a paper towel to dry for a minute, then roughly chop.\n\nStep 2: Make the sauce\nMake the stabilizing gel: add the cornstarch and water to a small saucepan. Mix together until dissolved. Turn the heat to low and, while whisking, bring it to just below a simmer. The starch should begin to thicken. Stir to ensure there are no clumps, then turn off the heat. Set aside. Add the spinach, garlic, cheese, olive oil, lemon juice, and as much fresh cracked black pepper as desired to a blender. Pulse once or twice. Pour in the cornstarch gel and blend everything together to create a stable emulsion of the cheese, pepper, and gel. Give it a taste, and add a touch of salt if needed. Store in the fridge for up to 3-4 days.\n\nStep 3: Boil noodles & mix pasta\nSet a pot of water to boil along with a big pinch of salt. Add the pasta and bring to a boil. Cook until slightly underdone, 1-2 minutes less than the package says. Reserve some of the pasta water. Set a second pan on the stove, but keep the heat off. Add 2 heaping spoonfuls of the spinach sauce along with a splash of the reserved pasta water. Mix together until smooth. With the heat still off, add the still-hot pasta. Turn the heat to medium-low and slowly bring up the temperature of the sauce while tossing with the pasta. Be a little careful of the heat, but this can come to a light simmer without breaking. Serve on a plate with more grated parm and some basil.","alternatives":[]}]}},{"event_type":"recipe_card","recipe":{"id":"r109","name":"Anything You Have Frittata","name_zh":"万能百搭烘蛋","cuisine":"American","cooking_method":"oven","effort_level":"medium","flavor_tags":["cheesy","herby","rich","savory"],"serves":1,"pcsv_roles":{"sauce":["cooking oil","milk","salt","sour cream","hot sauce"],"veggie":["aromatics","raw vegetables","herbs"],"protein":["meat, cooked & chopped","eggs","cheese"]},"ingredients_have":["raw vegetables"],"ingredients_need":["cooking oil","aromatics","meat, cooked & chopped","eggs","milk","salt","cheese","herbs","sour cream","hot sauce"],"ingredients":[{"name":"cooking oil","amount":"as needed","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"aromatics","amount":"variable","pcsv":["veggie"]},{"name":"raw vegetables","amount":"variable","pcsv":["veggie"]},{"name":"meat, cooked & chopped","amount":"variable","pcsv":["protein"]},{"name":"eggs","amount":"4-12","pcsv":["protein"]},{"name":"milk","amount":"60-180 g","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"salt","amount":"to taste","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"cheese","amount":"optional","pcsv":["protein"]},{"name":"herbs","amount":"optional","pcsv":["veggie"]},{"name":"sour cream","amount":"optional","pcsv":["sauce"]},{"name":"hot sauce","amount":"optional","pcsv":["sauce"]}],"instructions":"Step 1: Preheat oven to 400°F/204°C. Whisk eggs and milk with salt. Gather and chop meat, vegetables, and aromatic scraps.\n\nStep 2: Choose appropriately sized oven-safe pan. Add oil and sauté vegetables, aromatics, and meat over high heat until cooked and browned. Pour egg mixture into pan and distribute evenly. Transfer to larger pan if needed.\n\nStep 3: Bake 15-20 minutes until eggs are set. Frittata will puff slig